CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 29, 1946, pg. 21 reads: "Piscatorial - That means anything pertaining to fish. And 77-year-old John Champlin knows his business as this twenty-seven-pound husky attests.  It was caught in a lake at Aspinwall. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: John Champlin, standing between doorways, holding up a twenty-seven pound musky for woman measuring fish's mouth with her fingers
